docs.lead_paragraph: Little Italy, which really consists of a number of Little Italies scattered in various quarters of the city, was en fete yesterday. The Feast of the Assumption takes rank in the Latin countries with Christmas and Easter, and the Italians in New York are extremely tenacious of their customs, though the storekeepers did not shut up their shops yesterday.
